title: The Traveler
author: movinggarrett12
pages:
#-  CHAPTER 1

   He lays there, cold and confused. He finds himself surrounded by snow and stone. He has nothing but the clothes on his back.

   Cold and confused he heads off in a random direction with no sense of direction
#- or location. Scared and confused he hopes to find some sort of town, some sort of people, some sort of life.

CHAPTER 2

   He walked for several hours with no food or supplies. His hunger bar is low and
#- he starts feeling the pain. He climbs over a block hoping to find some sort of hope when suddenly he slips down the cliff.

   Taking massive fall damage he wonders if he will make it. He is down to two hearts and as his life slips away he sees a hope.
#- CHAPTER 3

   Far in the distance a furry savior appears, a cow. But as he looks even more he sees that it is not just one cow, but multiple cows.

  Full of joy he starts beating his hands with nothing but his bare hands. One by 
#- one all the cows die. With no coal or wood to cook the meat he eats the meat uncooked.

Stomach full and health back up he goes on. With a new sense of hope he travels on.
#- CHAPTER 4

   The first sign of hope appears before him, a sign. "A sign a sign!," he chants. He is filled with joy. The sign spoke, "Future spot of Ironside." Confused but full of joy he waited.


#- CHAPTER 5

   He waited and waited but nobody ever came. Full of sorrow and sadness he moved on.

   Although sadened by this it gave him please that there actualy was someone in this desolate land.
#- CHAPTER 6

  He traveled for many days and many nights with few signs of life here and there.

   He comes upon a house and screams with joy. As he approaches the house nobody is there. he looks around and 
#- find that the house is severely griefed and damaged. 

Seeing as there is no point to just leave it he decides to open the chest and take some supplies. Some sticks, food, coal, and some blocks. He is now off again.
#- CHAPTER 7

More days past and still no sign of life. The man starts to believe that there is no hope and that there is no point. Then suddenly there is a glow in the distance.... a light.
#- CHAPTER 8

With nothing left to hold him backs he sprints towards the light. As he runs towards it more and more lights appear, then a building, and more buildings, a town.

As he sprints in the town is bustling with
#- life everywhere. People trading, people runing, and people building.

A man comes up, Rykleos, and greets him. "Hello new friend! Welcome!" he says. "Where am I?" he asks Rykleos. He responds with one word simple word, Tigerstaden.
#- CHAPTER 9

  During the next few months our great traveler spent time building, making friends, and gaining wealth. He met great friends like Spartan, Ryk, REEL_KNEEGROW, and many others.

He builds a nice tidy 
#- little home next to his freindly neighbor. He starts giving supplies in exchange for iron. He finally completes his armor. He joins the extinction clan with his friend Rad.

  All is well, all is fun, and for once the world is quiet.
#- 




           THE

           WAR
#- CHAPTER 10

As our traveler sat in the market he over hears people talking. There is discusion of a war going on in one of the neighboring cities.

Our traveler listens silently trying to understand. "We need
#- to make a army," they say, "we wont survive theis raiders!"

Unaware of what is happening he ignores it and goes on in his day. His day is soon to change.


#- CHAPTER 11

As he relaxes in his house happy with the new level he had created he hears a cry. "HCF!" he hears and jumps to his feat!

   He runs for his sword and gets ready for battle. But as he starts running 
#- towards the fight Spartan stops him. "Run you idiot, its suicide! They have prot4 there is nothing you can do." Angry but understanding he ran to his home and logged.

   Feeling like a coward he hid and wept.
#- CHAPTER 12

  As everyone  prepared for war our traveler grew nervous. He was not experienced in pvp and was scared for his life. But he knew he had too revenge his friends.

   And so, they left.
#- CHAPTER 15

They travelled many days and nights. By boats and by feet. They travelled for hours on end till they reached there destination, the world border.
#- CHAPTER 16

    As we got there people instantly starting breaking the vault. A few wondered why there was no resistance but they were told they would regroup before the attack. It was cold and silent. Silence, it would soon be gone.
#- CHAPTER 17

  In charge of gaurding, our traveler sat waiting. Then he noticed something. Off below he saw something. A man by the name of Gordge. He asked them, "Leave!" but the man kept coming. As our traveller looked
#- farther he noticed he wasnt alone.

  Behind him stood more than thirty five men in enchanted armor. Deciding he best not sacrife himself he ran for back up.

As he made it back he ran yelled for back up and everyone 
#- gathered in front of the vault. Out armed but greater in numbers many peoples hopes were high. And as Gordge and his army approached all the men let and a great, "CHARGE,"  and engaged there forces.
#- CHAPTER 18

  As the battle consumed our traveler found himself consumed swinging at enemy to enemy. He fought and fought but it did no good.

   His friends fell left and right and as he looked on around ten
#- were left of them. He turned around and saw Gordge, eye to eye with them. He knew this would be it.

CHAPTER 19

   He started off by throwing poison at Gordge but he pearled past it and started swinging. Our 
#- traveler fought and fought but he was out matched.

   Low on health and nothing to lose he tried pearling away. But once he landed he was instantly hit behind. Gordge had pearled straight on him. Our young adventurer knew this 
#- was it. He swang his sword one more time but then fell to the sword of Gordge.

  He was stuck in the end, but it was not the end of his story. A new story would soon begin.
#- 


     COMING SOON



    THE TRAVELER

The Enemy Among Us
#- 